56 void R_RemapShader(const char *shaderName, const char *newShaderName, const char *timeOffset)
57 {
58  char strippedName[MAX_QPATH];
59  int hash;
60  shader_t *sh, *sh2;
61  qhandle_t h;
62 
63  sh = R_FindShaderByName(shaderName);
64  if (sh == NULL || sh == tr.defaultShader)
65  {
66  h = RE_RegisterShader(shaderName);
67  sh = R_GetShaderByHandle(h);
68  }
69  if (sh == NULL || sh == tr.defaultShader)
70  {
71  Ren_Warning("WARNING: R_RemapShader: shader %s not found\n", shaderName);
72  return;
73  }
74 
75  sh2 = R_FindShaderByName(newShaderName);
76  if (sh2 == NULL || sh2 == tr.defaultShader)
77  {
78  h = RE_RegisterShader(newShaderName);
79  sh2 = R_GetShaderByHandle(h);
80  }
81 
82  if (sh2 == NULL || sh2 == tr.defaultShader)
83  {
84  Ren_Warning("WARNING: R_RemapShader: new shader %s not found\n", newShaderName);
85  return;
86  }
87 
88  // remap all the shaders with the given name
89  // even tho they might have different lightmaps
90  COM_StripExtension(shaderName, strippedName, sizeof(strippedName));
91  hash = generateHashValue(strippedName, FILE_HASH_SIZE);
92  for (sh = shaderHashTable[hash]; sh; sh = sh->next)
93  {
94  if (Q_stricmp(sh->name, strippedName) == 0)
95  {
96  if (sh != sh2)
97  {
98  sh->remappedShader = sh2;
99  }
100  else
101  {
102  sh->remappedShader = NULL;
103  }
104  }
105  }
106 
107  if (timeOffset)
108  {
109  sh2->timeOffset = atoi(timeOffset);
110  }
111 }

124 static qboolean ParseVector(char **text, int count, float *v)
125 {
126  char *token;
127  int i;
128 
129  token = COM_ParseExt(text, qfalse);
130  if (strcmp(token, "("))
131  {
132  Ren_Warning("WARNING: missing parenthesis '(' in shader '%s' of token '%s'\n", shader.name, token);
133  return qfalse;
134  }
135 
136  for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
137  {
138  token = COM_ParseExt(text, qfalse);
139  if (!token[0])
140  {
141  Ren_Warning("WARNING: missing vector element in shader '%s' - no token\n", shader.name);
142  return qfalse;
143  }
144  v[i] = atof(token);
145  }
146 
147  token = COM_ParseExt(text, qfalse);
148  if (strcmp(token, ")"))
149  {
150  Ren_Warning("WARNING: missing parenthesis ')' in shader '%s' of token '%s'\n", shader.name, token);
151  return qfalse;
152  }
153 
154  return qtrue;
155 }

213 static void GetOpType(const char *token, expOperation_t *op)
214 {
215  const opstring_t *opString;
216  char tableName[MAX_QPATH];
217  int hash;
218  shaderTable_t *tb;
219 
220  if ((token[0] >= '0' && token[0] <= '9') ||
221  //(token[0] == '-' && token[1] >= '0' && token[1] <= '9') ||
222  //(token[0] == '+' && token[1] >= '0' && token[1] <= '9') ||
223  (token[0] == '.' && token[1] >= '0' && token[1] <= '9'))
224  {
225  op->type = OP_NUM;
226  return;
227  }
228 
229  Q_strncpyz(tableName, token, sizeof(tableName));
230  hash = generateHashValue(tableName, MAX_SHADERTABLE_HASH);
231 
232  for (tb = shaderTableHashTable[hash]; tb; tb = tb->next)
233  {
234  if (Q_stricmp(tb->name, tableName) == 0)
235  {
236  // match found
237  op->type = OP_TABLE;
238  op->value = tb->index;
239  return;
240  }
241  }
242 
243  for (opString = opStrings; opString->s; opString++)
244  {
245  if (!Q_stricmp(token, opString->s))
246  {
247  op->type = opString->type;
248  return;
249  }
250  }
251 
252  op->type = OP_BAD;
253 }

331 static int GetOpPrecedence(opcode_t oc)
332 {
333  switch (oc)
334  {
335  case OP_LOR:
336  return 1;
337  case OP_LAND:
338  return 2;
339  case OP_LEQ:
340  case OP_LNE:
341  return 3;
342  case OP_GE:
343  case OP_LE:
344  case OP_LT:
345  case OP_GT:
346  return 4;
347  case OP_ADD:
348  case OP_SUB:
349  return 5;
350  case OP_DIV:
351  case OP_MOD:
352  case OP_MUL:

368 static char *ParseExpressionElement(char **data_p)
369 {
370  int c = 0, len;
371  char *data;
372  const char **punc;
373  static char token[MAX_TOKEN_CHARS];
374  // multiple character punctuation tokens
375  const char *punctuation[] =
376  {
377  "&&", "||", "<=", ">=", "==", "!=", NULL
378  };
379 
380  if (!data_p)
381  {
382  Ren_Fatal("ParseExpressionElement: NULL data_p");
383  }
384 
385  data = *data_p;
386  len = 0;
387  token[0] = 0;
388 
389  // make sure incoming data is valid
390  if (!data)
391  {
392  *data_p = NULL;
393  return token;
394  }
395 
396  // skip whitespace
397  while (1)
398  {
399  // skip whitespace
400  while ((c = *data) <= ' ')
401  {
402  if (!c)
403  {
404  *data_p = NULL;
405  return token;
406  }
407  else if (c == '\n')
408  {
409  data++;
410  *data_p = data;
411  return token;
412  }
413  else
414  {
415  data++;
416  }
417  }
418 
419  c = *data;
420 
421  // skip double slash comments
422  if (c == '/' && data[1] == '/')
423  {
424  data += 2;
425  while (*data && *data != '\n')
426  {
427  data++;
428  }
429  }
430  // skip /* */ comments
431  else if (c == '/' && data[1] == '*')
432  {
433  data += 2;
434  while (*data && (*data != '*' || data[1] != '/'))
435  {
436  data++;
437  }
438  if (*data)
439  {
440  data += 2;
441  }
442  }
443  else
444  {
445  // a real token to parse
446  break;
447  }
448  }
449 
450  // handle quoted strings
451  if (c == '\"')
452  {
453  data++;
454  while (1)
455  {
456  c = *data++;
457 
458  if ((c == '\\') && (*data == '\"'))
459  {
460  // allow quoted strings to use \" to indicate the " character
461  data++;
462  }
463  else if (c == '\"' || !c)
464  {
465  token[len] = 0;
466  *data_p = (char *)data;
467  return token;
468  }
469 
470  if (len < MAX_TOKEN_CHARS - 1)
471  {
472  token[len] = c;
473  len++;
474  }
475  }
476  }
477 
478  // check for a number
479  if ((c >= '0' && c <= '9') ||
480  //(c == '-' && data[1] >= '0' && data[1] <= '9') ||
481  //(c == '+' && data[1] >= '0' && data[1] <= '9') ||
482  (c == '.' && data[1] >= '0' && data[1] <= '9'))
483  {
484  do
485  {
486  if (len < MAX_TOKEN_CHARS - 1)
487  {
488  token[len] = c;
489  len++;
490  }
491  data++;
492 
493  c = *data;
494  }
495  while ((c >= '0' && c <= '9') || c == '.');
496 
497  // parse the exponent
498  if (c == 'e' || c == 'E')
499  {
500  if (len < MAX_TOKEN_CHARS - 1)
501  {
502  token[len] = c;
503  len++;
504  }
505  data++;
506  c = *data;
507 
508  if (c == '-' || c == '+')
509  {
510  if (len < MAX_TOKEN_CHARS - 1)
511  {
512  token[len] = c;
513  len++;
514  }
515  data++;
516  c = *data;
517  }
518 
519  do
520  {
521  if (len < MAX_TOKEN_CHARS - 1)
522  {
523  token[len] = c;
524  len++;
525  }
526  data++;
527 
528  c = *data;
529  }
530  while (c >= '0' && c <= '9');
531  }
532 
533  if (len == MAX_TOKEN_CHARS)
534  {
535  len = 0;
536  }
537  token[len] = 0;
538 
539  *data_p = (char *)data;
540  return token;
541  }
542 
543  // check for a regular word
544  if ((c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') || (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') || (c == '_'))
545  {
546  do
547  {
548  if (len < MAX_TOKEN_CHARS - 1)
549  {
550  token[len] = c;
551  len++;
552  }
553  data++;
554 
555  c = *data;
556  }
557  while ((c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') || (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') || (c == '_') || (c >= '0' && c <= '9'));
558 
559  if (len == MAX_TOKEN_CHARS)
560  {
561  len = 0;
562  }
563  token[len] = 0;
564 
565  *data_p = (char *)data;
566  return token;
567  }
568 
569  // check for multi-character punctuation token
570  for (punc = punctuation; *punc; punc++)
571  {
572  int l;
573  int j;
574 
575  l = strlen(*punc);
576  for (j = 0; j < l; j++)
577  {
578  if (data[j] != (*punc)[j])
579  {
580  break;
581  }
582  }
583  if (j == l)
584  {
585  // a valid multi-character punctuation
586  Com_Memcpy(token, *punc, l);
587  token[l] = 0;
588  data += l;
589  *data_p = (char *)data;
590  return token;
591  }
592  }
593 
594  // single character punctuation
595  token[0] = *data;
596  token[1] = 0;
597  data++;
598  *data_p = (char *)data;
599 
600  return token;
601 }

608 static void ParseExpression(char **text, expression_t *exp)
609 {
610  int i;
611  char *token;
612  expOperation_t op, op2;
613  expOperation_t inFixOps[MAX_EXPRESSION_OPS];
614  int numInFixOps = 0;
615  // convert stack
616  expOperation_t tmpOps[MAX_EXPRESSION_OPS];
617  int numTmpOps = 0;
618 
619  exp->numOps = 0;
620 
621  // push left parenthesis on the stack
622  op.type = OP_LPAREN;
623  op.value = 0;
624  inFixOps[numInFixOps++] = op;
625 
626  while (1)
627  {
628  token = ParseExpressionElement(text);
629 
630  if (token[0] == 0 || token[0] == ',')
631  {
632  break;
633  }
634 
635  if (numInFixOps == MAX_EXPRESSION_OPS)
636  {
637  Ren_Print("WARNING: too many arithmetic expression operations in shader '%s'\n", shader.name);
638  SkipRestOfLine(text);
639  return;
640  }
641 
642  GetOpType(token, &op);
643 
644  switch (op.type)
645  {
646  case OP_BAD:
647  Ren_Print("WARNING: unknown token '%s' for arithmetic expression in shader '%s'\n", token,
648  shader.name);
649  break;
650  case OP_LBRACKET:
651  inFixOps[numInFixOps++] = op;
652 
653  // add extra (
654  op2.type = OP_LPAREN;
655  op2.value = 0;
656  inFixOps[numInFixOps++] = op2;
657  break;
658  case OP_RBRACKET:
659  // add extra )
660  op2.type = OP_RPAREN;
661  op2.value = 0;
662  inFixOps[numInFixOps++] = op2;
663 
664  inFixOps[numInFixOps++] = op;
665  break;
666  case OP_NUM:
667  op.value = atof(token);
668  inFixOps[numInFixOps++] = op;
669  break;
670  case OP_TABLE:
671  // value already set by GetOpType
672  inFixOps[numInFixOps++] = op;
673  break;
674  default:
675  op.value = 0;
676  inFixOps[numInFixOps++] = op;
677  break;
678  }
679  }
680 
681  // push right parenthesis on the stack
682  op.type = OP_RPAREN;
683  op.value = 0;
684  inFixOps[numInFixOps++] = op;
685 
686  for (i = 0; i < (numInFixOps - 1); i++)
687  {
688  op = inFixOps[i];
689  op2 = inFixOps[i + 1];
690 
691  // convert OP_SUBs that should be unary into OP_NEG
692  if (op2.type == OP_SUB && op.type != OP_RPAREN && op.type != OP_TABLE && !IsOperand(op.type))
693  {
694  inFixOps[i + 1].type = OP_NEG;
695  }
696  }
697 
698 #if 0
699  Ren_Print("infix:\n");
700  for (i = 0; i < numInFixOps; i++)
701  {
702  op = inFixOps[i];
703 
704  switch (op.type)
705  {
706  case OP_NUM:
707  Ren_Print("%f ", op.value);
708  break;
709  case OP_TABLE:
710  Ren_Print("%s ", tr.shaderTables[(int)op.value]->name);
711  break;
712  default:
713  Ren_Print("%s ", opStrings[op.type].s);
714  break;
715  }
716  }
717  Ren_Print("\n");
718 #endif
719 
720  // http://cis.stvincent.edu/swd/stl/stacks/stacks.html
721  // http://www.qiksearch.com/articles/cs/infix-postfix/
722  // http://www.experts-exchange.com/Programming/Programming_Languages/C/Q_20394130.html
723 
724  // convert infix representation to postfix
725 
726  for (i = 0; i < numInFixOps; i++)
727  {
728  op = inFixOps[i];
729 
730  // if current operator in infix is digit
731  if (IsOperand(op.type))
732  {
733  exp->ops[exp->numOps++] = op;
734  }
735  // if current operator in infix is left parenthesis
736  else if (op.type == OP_LPAREN)
737  {
738  tmpOps[numTmpOps++] = op;
739  }
740  // if current operator in infix is operator
741  else if (IsOperator(op.type))
742  {
743  while (1)
744  {
745  if (!numTmpOps)
746  {
747  Ren_Print("WARNING: invalid infix expression in shader '%s'\n", shader.name);
748  return;
749  }
750  else
751  {
752  // get top element
753  op2 = tmpOps[numTmpOps - 1];
754 
755  if (IsOperator(op2.type))
756  {
757  if (GetOpPrecedence(op2.type) >= GetOpPrecedence(op.type))
758  {
759  exp->ops[exp->numOps++] = op2;
760  numTmpOps--;
761  }
762  else
763  {
764  break;
765  }
766  }
767  else
768  {
769  break;
770  }
771  }
772  }
773 
774  tmpOps[numTmpOps++] = op;
775  }
776  // if current operator in infix is right parenthesis
777  else if (op.type == OP_RPAREN)
778  {
779  while (1)
780  {
781  if (!numTmpOps)
782  {
783  Ren_Print("WARNING: invalid infix expression in shader '%s'\n", shader.name);
784  return;
785  }
786  else
787  {
788  // get top element
789  op2 = tmpOps[numTmpOps - 1];
790 
791  if (op2.type != OP_LPAREN)
792  {
793  exp->ops[exp->numOps++] = op2;
794  numTmpOps--;
795  }
796  else
797  {
798  numTmpOps--;
799  break;
800  }
801  }
802  }
803  }
804  }
805 
806  // everything went ok
807  exp->active = qtrue;
808 
809 #if 0
810  Ren_Print("postfix:\n");
811  for (i = 0; i < exp->numOps; i++)
812  {
813  op = exp->ops[i];
814 
815  switch (op.type)
816  {
817  case OP_NUM:
818  Ren_Print("%f ", op.value);
819  break;
820  case OP_TABLE:
821  Ren_Print("%s ", tr.shaderTables[(int)op.value]->name);
822  break;
823  default:
824  Ren_Print("%s ", opStrings[op.type].s);
825  break;
826  }
827  }
828  Ren_Print("\n");
829 #endif
830 }

1026 void ParseStencil(char **text, stencil_t *stencil)
1027 {
1028  char *token;
1029 
1030  stencil->flags = 0;
1031  stencil->mask = stencil->writeMask = 0xff;
1032  stencil->ref = 1;
1033 
1034  // [mask <mask>]
1035  token = COM_ParseExt(text, qfalse);
1036 
1037  if (token[0] == 0)
1038  {
1039  Ren_Warning("WARNING: missing stencil ref value in shader '%s'\n", shader.name);
1040  return;
1041  }
1042 
1043  if (!Q_stricmp(token, "mask"))
1044  {
1045  token = COM_ParseExt(text, qfalse);
1046  if (token[0] == 0)
1047  {
1048  Ren_Warning("WARNING: missing stencil mask value in shader '%s'\n", shader.name);
1049  return;
1050  }
1051  stencil->mask = atoi(token);
1052 
1053  token = COM_ParseExt(text, qfalse);
1054  }
1055 
1056  if (token[0] == 0)
1057  {
1058  Ren_Warning("WARNING: missing stencil ref value in shader '%s'\n", shader.name);
1059  return;
1060  }
1061 
1062  if (!Q_stricmp(token, "writeMask"))
1063  {
1064  token = COM_ParseExt(text, qfalse);

1066  {
1067  Ren_Warning("WARNING: missing stencil writeMask value in shader '%s'\n", shader.name);
1068  return;
1069  }
1070  stencil->writeMask = atoi(token);
1071 
1072  token = COM_ParseExt(text, qfalse);
1073  }
1074 
1075  // <ref>
1076  if (token[0] == 0)
1077  {
1078  Ren_Warning("WARNING: missing stencil ref value in shader '%s'\n", shader.name);
1079  return;
1080  }
1081 
1082  stencil->ref = atoi(token);
1083 
1084  // <op>
1085  token = COM_ParseExt(text, qfalse);
1086 
1087  if (token[0] == 0)
1088  {
1089  Ren_Warning("WARNING: missing stencil test op in shader '%s'\n", shader.name);
1090  return;
1091  }

1093  {
1094  stencil->flags |= STF_ALWAYS;
1095  }
1096  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "never"))

1099  }

1103  }
1104  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "lequal"))
1105  {
1106  stencil->flags |= STF_LEQUAL;
1107  }
1108  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "greater"))
1109  {
1110  stencil->flags |= STF_GREATER;
1111  }
1112  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "gequal"))
1113  {
1114  stencil->flags |= STF_GEQUAL;
1115  }
1116  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "equal"))
1117  {
1118  stencil->flags |= STF_EQUAL;
1119  }
1120  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "nequal"))
1121  {
1122  stencil->flags |= STF_NEQUAL;
1123  }
1124  else
1125  {
1126  Ren_Warning("WARNING: missing stencil test op in shader '%s'\n", shader.name);
1127  return;
1128  }
1129 
1130  // <sfail>
1131  token = COM_ParseExt(text, qfalse);
1132 
1133  if (token[0] == 0)
1134  {
1135  Ren_Warning("WARNING: missing stencil sfail op in shader '%s'\n", shader.name);
1136  return;
1137  }
1138  stencil->flags |= NameToStencilOp(token) << STS_SFAIL;
1139 
1140  // <zfail>
1141  token = COM_ParseExt(text, qfalse);
1142 
1143  if (token[0] == 0)
1144  {
1145  Ren_Warning("WARNING: missing stencil zfail op in shader '%s'\n", shader.name);
1146  return;
1147  }
1148  stencil->flags |= NameToStencilOp(token) << STS_ZFAIL;
1149 
1150  // <zpass>
1151  token = COM_ParseExt(text, qfalse);
1152 
1153  if (token[0] == 0)
1154  {
1155  Ren_Warning("WARNING: missing stencil zpass op in shader '%s'\n", shader.name);
1156  return;
1157  }
1158  stencil->flags |= NameToStencilOp(token) << STS_ZPASS;
1159 }

1456 static qboolean ParseMap(shaderStage_t *stage, char **text, char *buffer, size_t bufferSize)
1457 {
1458  size_t len;
1459  char *token;
1460 
1461  // examples
1462  // map textures/caves/tembrick1crum_local.tga
1463  // addnormals (textures/caves/tembrick1crum_local.tga, heightmap (textures/caves/tembrick1crum_bmp.tga, 3 ))
1464  // heightmap( textures/hell/hellbones_d07bbump.tga, 8)
1465 
1466  while (1)
1467  {
1468  token = COM_ParseExt2(text, qfalse);
1469 
1470  if (!token[0])
1471  {
1472  // end of line
1473  break;
1474  }
1475 
1476  Q_strcat(buffer, bufferSize, token);
1477  Q_strcat(buffer, bufferSize, " ");
1478  }
1479 
1480  if (!buffer[0])
1481  {
1482  Ren_Warning("WARNING: 'map' missing parameter in shader '%s'\n", shader.name);
1483  return qfalse;
1484  }
1485 
1486  len = strlen(buffer);
1487  buffer[len - 1] = 0; // replace last ' ' with tailing zero
1488 
1489  return qtrue;
1490 }

1498 qboolean LoadMap(shaderStage_t *stage, char *buffer)
1499 {
1500  char *token;
1501  int imageBits = 0;
1502  filterType_t filterType;
1503  wrapType_t wrapType;
1504  char *buffer_p = &buffer[0];
1505 
1506  if (!buffer || !buffer[0])
1507  {
1508  Ren_Warning("WARNING: NULL parameter for LoadMap in shader '%s'\n", shader.name);
1509  return qfalse;
1510  }
1511 
1512  //Ren_Print("LoadMap: buffer '%s'\n", buffer);
1513 
1514  token = COM_ParseExt2(&buffer_p, qfalse);
1515 
1516  if (!Q_stricmp(token, "$whiteimage") || !Q_stricmp(token, "$white") || !Q_stricmp(token, "_white") ||
1517  !Q_stricmp(token, "*white"))
1518  {
1519  stage->bundle[0].image[0] = tr.whiteImage;
1520  return qtrue;
1521  }
1522  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "$blackimage") || !Q_stricmp(token, "$black") || !Q_stricmp(token, "_black") ||
1523  !Q_stricmp(token, "*black"))
1524  {
1525  stage->bundle[0].image[0] = tr.blackImage;
1526  return qtrue;
1527  }
1528  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "$flatimage") || !Q_stricmp(token, "$flat") || !Q_stricmp(token, "_flat") ||
1529  !Q_stricmp(token, "*flat"))
1530  {
1531  stage->bundle[0].image[0] = tr.flatImage;
1532  return qtrue;
1533  }
1534  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "$lightmap"))
1535  {
1536  stage->type = ST_LIGHTMAP;
1537  return qtrue;
1538  }
1539  //skip normalmap on sky .... for now
1540  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "sky") )
1541  {
1542  imageBits |= !IF_NORMALMAP;
1543  }
1544 
1545  // determine image options
1546  if (stage->overrideNoPicMip || shader.noPicMip || stage->highQuality || stage->forceHighQuality)
1547  {
1548  imageBits |= IF_NOPICMIP;
1549  }
1550 
1551  if (stage->type == ST_NORMALMAP || stage->type == ST_HEATHAZEMAP || stage->type == ST_LIQUIDMAP)
1552  {
1553  imageBits |= IF_NORMALMAP;
1554  }
1555 
1556  if (stage->type == ST_NORMALMAP && shader.parallax)
1557  {
1558  imageBits |= IF_DISPLACEMAP;
1559  }
1560 
1561  if (stage->uncompressed || stage->highQuality || stage->forceHighQuality || shader.uncompressed)
1562  {
1563  imageBits |= IF_NOCOMPRESSION;
1564  }
1565 
1566  if (stage->forceHighQuality)
1567  {
1568  imageBits |= IF_NOCOMPRESSION;
1569  }
1570 
1571  if (stage->stateBits & (GLS_ATEST_BITS))
1572  {
1573  imageBits |= IF_ALPHATEST;
1574  }
1575 
1576  if (stage->overrideFilterType)
1577  {
1578  filterType = stage->filterType;
1579  }
1580  else
1581  {
1582  filterType = shader.filterType;
1583  }
1584 
1585  if (stage->overrideWrapType)
1586  {
1587  wrapType = stage->wrapType;
1588  }
1589  else
1590  {
1591  wrapType = shader.wrapType;
1592  }
1593 
1594  // try to load the image
1595  stage->bundle[0].image[0] = R_FindImageFile(buffer, imageBits, filterType, wrapType, shader.name);
1596

1601  //makes terrain black and orange,also on some
1602  //maps loads model textures it didnt before.
1603  //better just to print a warning for now
1604  return qfalse;
1605  }
1606 
1607 
1608  // try to load additional normal and specular images & create stages (r1 shader compatible mode/treat COLORMAPS as DIFFUSEMAPS)
1609  // - if this stage isn't already a normal map or a specular map (FIXME & test)
1610  // - also check the stageOffset stage and don't overwrite existing stages !!!
1611  if (stage->type == ST_DIFFUSEMAP && shader.type != SHADER_2D && shader.type != SHADER_LIGHT && r_normalMapping->integer > 0 && !(imageBits & IF_NORMALMAP))
1612  //if (stage->type == ST_DIFFUSEMAP && shader.type != SHADER_2D && shader.type != SHADER_LIGHT && r_normalMapping->integer > 0)
1613  //if (shader.type != SHADER_2D && shader.type != SHADER_LIGHT && r_normalMapping->integer > 0 && !(imageBits & IF_NORMALMAP))
1614  {
1615  // image loading of
1616  image_t *tmpImage;
1617  int stageOffset = 1;
1618  char strippedName[MAX_QPATH];
1619 
1620  COM_StripExtension(buffer, strippedName, sizeof(strippedName));
1621  COM_FixPath(strippedName);
1622 
1623  // Note/FIXME: image file name has to be including extension, we use tga - make this more generic one day
1624  // ETL: suffix for normalmaps is '_n'
1625  tmpImage = R_FindImageFile(va("%s_n.tga", strippedName), imageBits, filterType, wrapType, shader.name);
1626  if (tmpImage)

1629  stages[stageOffset].bundle[0].image[0] = tmpImage;
1630  stages[stageOffset].type = ST_NORMALMAP;
1631  stages[stageOffset].rgbGen = CGEN_IDENTITY;
1632  stages[stageOffset].stateBits = GLS_DEFAULT;
1633  stageOffset++;
1634  }
1635  else
1636  {

1638  }
1639 
1640  // Note/FIXME: image file name has to be including extension, we use tga - make this more generic one day
1641  // ETL: suffix for specularmaps is '_r'
1642  tmpImage = R_FindImageFile(va("%s_r.tga", strippedName), imageBits, filterType, wrapType, shader.name);
1643  if (tmpImage)
1644  {
1645  stages[stageOffset].active = qtrue;
1646  stages[stageOffset].bundle[0].image[0] = tmpImage;
1647  stages[stageOffset].type = ST_SPECULARMAP;
1648  stages[stageOffset].rgbGen = CGEN_IDENTITY;
1649  stages[stageOffset].stateBits = GLS_DEFAULT;
1650  stageOffset++;
1651  }
1652  else
1653  {
1654  Ren_Developer("LoadMap Warning: Specularmap image '%s' type %i not found.\n", va("%s_r.tga", strippedName), shader.type);
1655  }
1656  }
1657 
1658  return qtrue;
1659 }

2829 
2843 void ParseDeform(char **text)
2844 {
2845  char *token;
2846  deformStage_t *ds;
2847 
2848  token = COM_ParseExt2(text, qfalse);
2849  if (token[0] == 0)
2850  {
2851  Ren_Warning("WARNING: missing deform parm in shader '%s'\n", shader.name);
2852  return;
2853  }
2854 
2855  if (shader.numDeforms == MAX_SHADER_DEFORMS)
2856  {
2857  Ren_Warning("WARNING: MAX_SHADER_DEFORMS in '%s'\n", shader.name);
2858  return;
2859  }
2860 
2861  ds = &shader.deforms[shader.numDeforms];
2862  shader.numDeforms++;
2863 
2864  if (!Q_stricmp(token, "projectionShadow"))
2865  {
2866  ds->deformation = DEFORM_PROJECTION_SHADOW;
2867  return;
2868  }
2869  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "autosprite"))
2870  {
2871  ds->deformation = DEFORM_AUTOSPRITE;
2872  return;
2873  }
2874  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "autosprite2"))
2875  {
2876  ds->deformation = DEFORM_AUTOSPRITE2;
2877  return;
2878  }
2879  else if (!Q_stricmpn(token, "text", 4))
2880  {
2881  int n;
2882 
2883  n = token[4] - '0';
2884  if (n < 0 || n > 7)
2885  {
2886  n = 0;
2887  }
2888  ds->deformation = (deform_t)(DEFORM_TEXT0 + n);
2889  return;
2890  }
2891  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "bulge"))
2892  {
2893  token = COM_ParseExt2(text, qfalse);
2894  if (token[0] == 0)
2895  {
2896  Ren_Warning("WARNING: missing deformVertexes bulge parm in shader '%s'\n", shader.name);
2897  return;
2898  }
2899  ds->bulgeWidth = atof(token);
2900 
2901  token = COM_ParseExt2(text, qfalse);
2902  if (token[0] == 0)
2903  {

3452 static char *FindGuideInGuideText(const char *guideName)
3453 {
3454  char *token, *p;
3455 
3456  int i, hash;
3457 
3458  if (!s_guideText)
3459  {
3460  // no guides loaded at all
3461  return NULL;
3462  }
3463 
3464  hash = generateHashValue(guideName, MAX_GUIDETEXT_HASH);
3465 
3466  for (i = 0; guideTextHashTable[hash][i]; i++)
3467  {
3468  p = guideTextHashTable[hash][i];
3469  token = COM_ParseExt2(&p, qtrue);
3470  if (!Q_stricmp(token, guideName))
3471  {
3472  //Ren_Print("found guide '%s' by hashing\n", guideName);
3473  return p;
3474  }
3475  }
3476 
3477  p = s_guideText;
3478 
3479  if (!p)
3480  {
3481  return NULL;
3482  }
3483 
3484  // look for label
3485  while (1)
3486  {
3487  token = COM_ParseExt2(&p, qtrue);
3488  if (token[0] == 0)
3489  {
3490  break;
3491  }
3492 
3493  if (Q_stricmp(token, "guide") && Q_stricmp(token, "inlineGuide"))
3494  {
3495  Ren_Warning("WARNING: expected guide or inlineGuide found '%s'\n", token);
3496  break;
3497  }
3498 
3499  // parse guide name
3500  token = COM_ParseExt2(&p, qtrue);
3501 
3502  if (!Q_stricmp(token, guideName))
3503  {
3504  Ren_Print("found guide '%s' by linear search\n", guideName);
3505  return p;
3506  }
3507 
3508  // skip parameters
3509  token = COM_ParseExt2(&p, qtrue);
3510  if (Q_stricmp(token, "("))
3511  {
3512  Ren_Warning("WARNING: expected ( found '%s'\n", token);
3513  break;
3514  }
3515 
3516  while (1)
3517  {
3518  token = COM_ParseExt2(&p, qtrue);
3519 
3520  if (!token[0])
3521  {
3522  break;
3523  }
3524 
3525  if (!Q_stricmp(token, ")"))
3526  {
3527  break;
3528  }
3529  }
3530 
3531  if (Q_stricmp(token, ")"))
3532  {
3533  Ren_Warning("WARNING: expected ) found '%s'\n", token);
3534  break;
3535  }
3536 
3537  // skip guide body
3538  SkipBracedSection(&p);
3539  }
3540 
3541  return NULL;
3542 }

3777  {
3778  if (!(_text = CreateShaderByGuide(token, _text)))
3779  {
3780  Ren_Warning("WARNING: couldn't create shader '%s' by template '%s'\n", shader.name, token);

3796  return qfalse;
3797  }
3798 
3799  // end of shader definition
3800  if (token[0] == '}')
3801  {
3802  break;

4925 static void SortNewShader(void)
4926 {
4927  int i;
4928  shader_t *newShader = tr.shaders[tr.numShaders - 1];
4929 
4930  for (i = tr.numShaders - 2; i >= 0; i--)
4931  {
4932  if (tr.sortedShaders[i]->sort <= newShader->sort)
4933  {
4934  break;
4935  }
4936  tr.sortedShaders[i + 1] = tr.sortedShaders[i];
4937  tr.sortedShaders[i + 1]->sortedIndex++;
4938  }
4939 
4940  newShader->sortedIndex = i + 1;
4941  tr.sortedShaders[i + 1] = newShader;
4942 }

4985  break;
4986  }
4987  newShader->stages[i] = (shaderStage_t *)ri.Hunk_Alloc(sizeof(stages[i]), h_low);
4988  *newShader->stages[i] = stages[i];
4989 
4990  for (b = 0; b < MAX_TEXTURE_BUNDLES; b++)
4991  {
4992  size = newShader->stages[i]->bundle[b].numTexMods * sizeof(texModInfo_t);

4994  Com_Memcpy(newShader->stages[i]->bundle[b].texMods, stages[i].bundle[b].texMods, size);
4995  }
4996  }
4997 
4998  SortNewShader();
4999 
5000  hash = generateHashValue(newShader->name, FILE_HASH_SIZE);
5001  newShader->next = shaderHashTable[hash];
5002  shaderHashTable[hash] = newShader;
5003 
5004  return newShader;
5005 }

5058 static shader_t *FinishShader(void)
5059 {
5060  int stage, i;
5061 
5062  // set sky stuff appropriate
5063  if (shader.isSky)
5064  {
5065  if (shader.noFog)
5066  {
5067  shader.sort = SS_ENVIRONMENT_NOFOG;
5068  }
5069  else
5070  {
5071  shader.sort = SS_ENVIRONMENT_FOG;
5072  }
5073  }
5074 
5075  if (shader.forceOpaque)
5076  {
5077  shader.sort = SS_OPAQUE;
5078  }
5079 
5080  // set polygon offset
5081  if (shader.polygonOffset && shader.sort == SS_BAD)
5082  {
5083  shader.sort = SS_DECAL;
5084  }
5085 
5086  // all light materials need at least one z attenuation stage as first stage
5087  if (shader.type == SHADER_LIGHT)
5088  {
5089  if (stages[0].type != ST_ATTENUATIONMAP_Z)
5090  {
5091  // move up subsequent stages
5092  memmove(&stages[1], &stages[0], sizeof(stages[0]) * (MAX_SHADER_STAGES - 1));
5093 
5094  stages[0].active = qtrue;
5095  stages[0].type = ST_ATTENUATIONMAP_Z;
5096  stages[0].rgbGen = CGEN_IDENTITY;
5097  stages[0].stateBits = GLS_DEFAULT;
5098  stages[0].overrideWrapType = qtrue;
5099  stages[0].wrapType = WT_EDGE_CLAMP;
5100 
5101  LoadMap(&stages[0], "lights/squarelight1a.tga"); // we have png in path
5102  }
5103 
5104  // force following shader stages to be xy attenuation stages
5105  for (stage = 1; stage < MAX_SHADER_STAGES; stage++)
5106  {
5107  shaderStage_t *pStage = &stages[stage];
5108 
5109  if (!pStage->active)
5110  {
5111  break;
5112  }
5113 
5114  pStage->type = ST_ATTENUATIONMAP_XY;
5115  }
5116  }
5117 
5118  // set appropriate stage information
5119  for (stage = 0; stage < MAX_SHADER_STAGES; stage++)
5120  {
5121  shaderStage_t *pStage = &stages[stage];
5122 
5123  if (!pStage->active)
5124  {
5125  break;
5126  }
5127 
5128  // check for a missing texture
5129  switch (pStage->type)
5130  {
5131  case ST_LIQUIDMAP:
5132  case ST_LIGHTMAP:
5133  // skip
5134  break;
5135  case ST_COLORMAP:
5136  default:
5137  {
5138  if (!pStage->bundle[0].image[0])
5139  {
5140  Ren_Warning("Shader %s has a colormap stage with no image or an invalid stage type - stage isn't active\n", shader.name);
5141  pStage->active = qfalse;
5142  continue;
5143  }
5144  break;
5145  }
5146  case ST_DIFFUSEMAP:
5147  {
5148  if (!shader.isSky)
5149  {
5150  shader.interactLight = qtrue;
5151  }
5152 
5153  if (!pStage->bundle[0].image[0])
5154  {
5155  Ren_Warning("Shader %s has a diffusemap stage with no image - default image set\n", shader.name);
5156  pStage->bundle[0].image[0] = tr.defaultImage;
5157  }
5158  break;
5159  }
5160  case ST_NORMALMAP:
5161  {
5162  if (!shader.isSky)
5163  {
5164  shader.interactLight = qtrue;
5165  }
5166 
5167  if (!pStage->bundle[0].image[0])
5168  {
5169  Ren_Warning("Shader %s has a normalmap stage with no image - flat image set\n", shader.name);
5170  pStage->bundle[0].image[0] = tr.flatImage;
5171  }
5172  break;
5173  }
5174  case ST_SPECULARMAP:
5175  {
5176  if (!pStage->bundle[0].image[0])
5177  {
5178  Ren_Warning("Shader %s has a specularmap stage with no image - black image set\n", shader.name);
5179  pStage->bundle[0].image[0] = tr.blackImage;
5180  }
5181  break;
5182  }
5183  case ST_ATTENUATIONMAP_XY:
5184  {
5185  if (!pStage->bundle[0].image[0])
5186  {
5187  Ren_Warning("Shader %s has an xy attenuationmap stage with no image - stage isn't active\n", shader.name);
5188  pStage->active = qfalse;
5189  continue;
5190  }
5191  break;
5192  }
5193  case ST_ATTENUATIONMAP_Z:
5194  {
5195  if (!pStage->bundle[0].image[0])
5196  {
5197  Ren_Warning("Shader %s has a z attenuationmap stage with no image - stage isn't active\n", shader.name);
5198  pStage->active = qfalse;
5199  continue;
5200  }
5201  break;
5202  }
5203  }
5204 
5205  // ditch this stage if it's detail and detail textures are disabled
5206 
5207  if (pStage->isDetail && !r_detailTextures->integer)
5208  {
5209  if (stage < (MAX_SHADER_STAGES - 1))
5210  {
5211  memmove(pStage, pStage + 1, sizeof(*pStage) * (MAX_SHADER_STAGES - stage - 1));
5212  // kill the last stage, since it's now a duplicate
5213  for (i = MAX_SHADER_STAGES - 1; i > stage; i--)
5214  {
5215  if (stages[i].active)
5216  {
5217  Com_Memset(&stages[i], 0, sizeof(*pStage));
5218  break;
5219  }
5220  }
5221  stage--; // the next stage is now the current stage, so check it again
5222  }
5223  else
5224  {
5225  Com_Memset(pStage, 0, sizeof(*pStage));
5226  }
5227  continue;
5228  }
5229 
5230  if (shader.forceOpaque)
5231  {
5232  pStage->stateBits |= GLS_DEPTHMASK_TRUE;
5233  }
5234 
5235  if (shader.isSky && pStage->noFog)
5236  {
5237  shader.sort = SS_ENVIRONMENT_NOFOG;
5238  }
5239 
5240  // determine sort order and fog color adjustment
5241  if ((pStage->stateBits & (GLS_SRCBLEND_BITS | GLS_DSTBLEND_BITS)) &&
5242  (stages[0].stateBits & (GLS_SRCBLEND_BITS | GLS_DSTBLEND_BITS)))
5243  {
5244  int blendSrcBits = pStage->stateBits & GLS_SRCBLEND_BITS;
5245  int blendDstBits = pStage->stateBits & GLS_DSTBLEND_BITS;
5246 
5247  // fog color adjustment only works for blend modes that have a contribution
5248  // that aproaches 0 as the modulate values aproach 0 --
5249  // GL_ONE, GL_ONE
5250  // GL_ZERO, GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC_COLOR
5251  // GL_SRC_ALPHA, GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA
5252 
5253  // modulate, additive
5254  if (((blendSrcBits == GLS_SRCBLEND_ONE) && (blendDstBits == GLS_DSTBLEND_ONE)) ||
5255  ((blendSrcBits == GLS_SRCBLEND_ZERO) && (blendDstBits == GLS_DSTBLEND_ONE_MINUS_SRC_COLOR)))
5256  {
5257  pStage->adjustColorsForFog = ACFF_MODULATE_RGB;
5258  }
5259  // strict blend
5260  else if ((blendSrcBits == GLS_SRCBLEND_SRC_ALPHA) &&
5261  (blendDstBits == GLS_DSTBLEND_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA))
5262  {
5263  pStage->adjustColorsForFog = ACFF_MODULATE_ALPHA;
5264  }
5265  // premultiplied alpha
5266  else if ((blendSrcBits == GLS_SRCBLEND_ONE) && (blendDstBits == GLS_DSTBLEND_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA))
5267  {
5268  pStage->adjustColorsForFog = ACFF_MODULATE_RGBA;
5269  }
5270  else
5271  {
5272  // we can't adjust this one correctly, so it won't be exactly correct in fog
5273  }
5274 
5275  // don't screw with sort order if this is a portal or environment
5276  if (shader.sort == SS_BAD)
5277  {
5278  // see through item, like a grill or grate
5279  if (pStage->stateBits & GLS_DEPTHMASK_TRUE)
5280  {
5281  shader.sort = SS_SEE_THROUGH;
5282  }
5283  else
5284  {
5285  shader.sort = SS_BLEND0;
5286  }
5287  }
5288  }
5289  }
5290  shader.numStages = stage;
5291 
5292  // there are times when you will need to manually apply a sort to
5293  // opaque alpha tested shaders that have later blend passes
5294  if (shader.sort == SS_BAD)
5295  {
5296  if (shader.translucent && !shader.forceOpaque)
5297  {
5298  shader.sort = SS_DECAL;
5299  }
5300  else
5301  {
5302  shader.sort = SS_OPAQUE;
5303  }
5304  }
5305 
5306 
5307  // HACK: allow alpha tested surfaces to create shadowmaps
5308  if (r_shadows->integer >= SHADOWING_ESM16)
5309  {
5310  if (shader.noShadows && shader.alphaTest)
5311  {
5312  shader.noShadows = qfalse;
5313  }
5314  }
5315 
5316  // look for multitexture potential
5317  CollapseStages();
5318 
5319  // fogonly shaders don't have any normal passes
5320  if (shader.numStages == 0 && !shader.isSky)
5321  {
5322  shader.sort = SS_FOG;
5323  }
5324 
5325  return GeneratePermanentShader();
5326 }

5335 qboolean RE_LoadDynamicShader(const char *shadername, const char *shadertext)
5336 {
5337  const char *func_err = "WARNING: RE_LoadDynamicShader";
5338  dynamicShader_t *dptr, *lastdptr;
5339  char *q, *token;
5340 
5341  Ren_Warning("RE_LoadDynamicShader( name = '%s', text = '%s' )\n", shadername, shadertext);
5342 
5343  if (!shadername && shadertext)
5344  {
5345  Ren_Warning("%s called with NULL shadername and non-NULL shadertext:\n%s\n", func_err, shadertext);
5346  return qfalse;
5347  }
5348 
5349  if (shadername && strlen(shadername) >= MAX_QPATH)
5350  {
5351  Ren_Warning("%s shadername %s exceeds MAX_QPATH\n", func_err, shadername);
5352  return qfalse;
5353  }
5354 
5355  // empty the whole list
5356  if (!shadername && !shadertext)
5357  {
5358  dptr = dshader;
5359  while (dptr)
5360  {
5361  lastdptr = dptr->next;
5362  ri.Free(dptr->shadertext);
5363  ri.Free(dptr);
5364  dptr = lastdptr;
5365  }
5366  dshader = NULL;
5367  return qtrue;
5368  }
5369 
5370  // walk list for existing shader to delete, or end of the list
5371  dptr = dshader;
5372  lastdptr = NULL;
5373  while (dptr)
5374  {
5375  q = dptr->shadertext;
5376 
5377  token = COM_ParseExt(&q, qtrue);
5378 
5379  if ((token[0] != 0) && !Q_stricmp(token, shadername))
5380  {
5381  //request to nuke this dynamic shader
5382  if (!shadertext)
5383  {
5384  if (!lastdptr)
5385  {
5386  dshader = NULL;
5387  }
5388  else
5389  {
5390  lastdptr->next = dptr->next;
5391  }
5392  ri.Free(dptr->shadertext);
5393  ri.Free(dptr);
5394  return qtrue;
5395  }
5396  Ren_Warning("%s shader %s already exists!\n", func_err, shadername);
5397  return qfalse;
5398  }
5399  lastdptr = dptr;
5400  dptr = dptr->next;
5401  }
5402 
5403  // cant add a new one with empty shadertext
5404  if (!shadertext || !strlen(shadertext))
5405  {
5406  Ren_Warning("%s new shader %s has NULL shadertext!\n", func_err, shadername);
5407  return qfalse;
5408  }
5409 
5410  // create a new shader
5411  dptr = (dynamicShader_t *) ri.Z_Malloc(sizeof(*dptr));
5412  if (!dptr)
5413  {
5414  Ren_Fatal("Couldn't allocate struct for dynamic shader %s\n", shadername);
5415  }
5416  if (lastdptr)
5417  {
5418  lastdptr->next = dptr;
5419  }
5420  dptr->shadertext = (char *)ri.Z_Malloc(strlen(shadertext) + 1);
5421  if (!dptr->shadertext)
5422  {
5423  Ren_Fatal("Couldn't allocate buffer for dynamic shader %s\n", shadername);
5424  }
5425  Q_strncpyz(dptr->shadertext, shadertext, strlen(shadertext) + 1);
5426  dptr->next = NULL;
5427  if (!dshader)
5428  {
5429  dshader = dptr;
5430  }
5431 
5432  //ri.Printf( PRINT_ALL, "Loaded dynamic shader [%s] with shadertext [%s]\n", shadername, shadertext );
5433 
5434  return qtrue;
5435 }

5445 static char *FindShaderInShaderText(const char *shaderName)
5446 {
5447  char *token, *p;
5448  int i, hash;
5449 
5450  // if we have any dynamic shaders loaded, check them first
5451  if (dshader)
5452  {
5453  dynamicShader_t *dptr = dshader;
5454  char *q;
5455  i = 0;
5456 
5457  while (dptr)
5458  {
5459  if (!dptr->shadertext || !strlen(dptr->shadertext))
5460  {
5461  Ren_Warning("WARNING: dynamic shader %s(%d) has no shadertext\n", shaderName, i);
5462  }
5463  else
5464  {
5465  q = dptr->shadertext;
5466 
5467  token = COM_ParseExt(&q, qtrue);
5468 
5469  if ((token[0] != 0) && !Q_stricmp(token, shaderName))
5470  {
5471  //ri.Printf( PRINT_ALL, "Found dynamic shader [%s] with shadertext [%s]\n", shadername, dptr->shadertext );
5472  return q;
5473  }
5474  }
5475  i++;
5476  dptr = dptr->next;
5477  }
5478  }
5479 
5480  hash = generateHashValue(shaderName, MAX_SHADERTEXT_HASH);
5481 
5482  for (i = 0; shaderTextHashTable[hash][i]; i++)
5483  {
5484  p = shaderTextHashTable[hash][i];
5485  token = COM_ParseExt2(&p, qtrue);
5486  if (!Q_stricmp(token, shaderName))
5487  {
5488  //Ren_Print("found shader '%s' by hashing\n", shaderName);
5489  return p;
5490  }
5491  }
5492 
5493  p = s_shaderText;
5494 
5495  if (!p)
5496  {
5497  return NULL;
5498  }
5499 
5500  // look for label
5501  while (1)
5502  {
5503  token = COM_ParseExt2(&p, qtrue);
5504  if (token[0] == 0)
5505  {
5506  break;
5507  }
5508 
5509  if (!Q_stricmp(token, shaderName))
5510  {
5511  //Ren_Print("found shader '%s' by linear search\n", shaderName);
5512  return p;
5513  }
5514  // skip shader tables
5515  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "table"))
5516  {
5517  // skip table name
5518  (void) COM_ParseExt2(&p, qtrue);
5519 
5520  SkipBracedSection(&p);
5521  }
5522  // support shader templates
5523  else if (!Q_stricmp(token, "guide"))
5524  {
5525  // parse shader name
5526  token = COM_ParseExt2(&p, qtrue);
5527 
5528  if (!Q_stricmp(token, shaderName))
5529  {
5530  Ren_Print("found shader '%s' by linear search\n", shaderName);
5531  return p;
5532  }
5533 
5534  // skip guide name
5535  token = COM_ParseExt2(&p, qtrue);
5536 
5537  // skip parameters
5538  token = COM_ParseExt2(&p, qtrue);
5539  if (Q_stricmp(token, "("))
5540  {
5541  break;
5542  }
5543 
5544  while (1)
5545  {
5546  token = COM_ParseExt2(&p, qtrue);
5547 
5548  if (!token[0])
5549  {
5550  break;
5551  }
5552 
5553  if (!Q_stricmp(token, ")"))
5554  {
5555  break;
5556  }
5557  }
5558 
5559  if (Q_stricmp(token, ")"))
5560  {
5561  break;
5562  }
5563  }
5564  else
5565  {
5566  // skip the shader body
5567  SkipBracedSection(&p);
5568  }
5569  }
5570 
5571  return NULL;
5572 }

5638 shader_t *R_FindShader(const char *name, shaderType_t type, qboolean mipRawImage)

5930 qhandle_t RE_RegisterShaderFromImage(const char *name, image_t *image, qboolean mipRawImage)
5931 {
5932  char strippedName[MAX_QPATH];
5933  int i, hash;
5934  shader_t *sh;
5935 
5936  if (strlen(name) >= MAX_QPATH)
5937  {
5938  Ren_Warning("RE_RegisterShaderFromImage WARNING: shader name exceeds MAX_QPATH\n");
5939  return 0;
5940  }
5941 
5942  COM_StripExtension(name, strippedName, sizeof(strippedName));
5943  COM_FixPath(strippedName);
5944 
5945  hash = generateHashValue(strippedName, FILE_HASH_SIZE);
5946 
5947  // see if the shader is already loaded
5948  for (sh = shaderHashTable[hash]; sh; sh = sh->next)
5949  {
5950  // NOTE: if there was no shader or image available with the name strippedName
5951  // then a default shader is created with type == SHADER_3D_DYNAMIC, so we
5952  // have to check all default shaders otherwise for every call to R_FindShader
5953  // with that same strippedName a new default shader is created.
5954  if ((sh->type == SHADER_2D || sh->defaultShader) && !Q_stricmp(sh->name, strippedName))
5955  {
5956  // match found
5957  return sh->index;
5958  }
5959  }
5960 
5961  // clear the global shader
5962  Com_Memset(&shader, 0, sizeof(shader));
5963  Com_Memset(&stages, 0, sizeof(stages));
5964  Q_strncpyz(shader.name, strippedName, sizeof(shader.name));
5965  shader.type = SHADER_2D;
5966  for (i = 0; i < MAX_SHADER_STAGES; i++)
5967  {
5968  stages[i].bundle[0].texMods = texMods[i];
5969  }
5970 
5971  // create the default shading commands
5972 
5973  // GUI elements
5974  stages[0].bundle[0].image[0] = image;
5975  stages[0].active = qtrue;
5976  stages[0].rgbGen = CGEN_VERTEX;
5977  stages[0].alphaGen = AGEN_VERTEX;
5978  stages[0].stateBits = GLS_DEPTHTEST_DISABLE | GLS_SRCBLEND_SRC_ALPHA | GLS_DSTBLEND_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA;
5979 
5980  sh = FinishShader();
5981  return sh->index;
5982 }
